    <div class="panel-group accordion" id="accordion">
        <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title pannel_bg_blue">
                    <span class="option_icons"><i class="fa fa-file-pdf-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> <i class="fa fa-print" aria-hidden="true"></i></span>
                    <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse4"><i class="fa fa-mouse-pointer fa-fw text-muted"></i> Navigation Help</a>
                </h4>
            </div>
            <div id="collapse4" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                <div class="panel-body">
                    <h4><i class="fa fa-list-alt" aria-hidden="true"></i> Navigation Bar</h4>
                    <p>
                        Can be found on the far right-side of your screen.  Contains: Ticker, Dashboard, Systems, 4-Chart, Single Chart (1, 2, 3), Research, Help, and Account links.
                    </p>
                    <h4><i class="fa fa-list-alt" aria-hidden="true"></i> Top Ticker</h4>
                    <p>Contains price quotes for the major markets.  The ticker can be toggled Open/Close from the “Arrow” icon on the side-navigation bar.</p>
                    <h4><i class="fa fa-list-alt" aria-hidden="true"></i> Dashboard</h4>
                    <p>This is the default screen.  Contains: “Market Overview”, “Hot Lists”, “Symbol Overview”, and “Economic Calendar” windows.</p>
                    <h4><i class="fa fa-list-alt" aria-hidden="true"></i> Systems </h4>
                    <p>Contains the BluSignals system screens: BluFractal, BluNeural, Combo, and BluQuant. </p>
                    <h4><i class="fa fa-list-alt" aria-hidden="true"></i> 4-Chart Screen </h4>
                    <p>Contains 4 independent price chart windows with technical analysis studies and drawing tools. </p>
                    <h4><i class="fa fa-list-alt" aria-hidden="true"></i> Single Chart Screens (1, 2, 3) </h4>
                    <p>Contains a price chart window with technical analysis studies and drawing tools.  And a fundamental chart window for the selected security. </p>
                    <h4><i class="fa fa-list-alt" aria-hidden="true"></i> Research Screen </h4>
                    <p>Contains a MarketWatch portal for investment news and information. </p>
                </div>
                @*<div class="panel-footer">Panel Footer</div>*@
            </div>
        </div>
            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <div class="panel-heading">
                    <h4 class="panel-title pannel_bg_blue">
                        <span class="option_icons"><i class="fa fa-file-pdf-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> <i class="fa fa-print" aria-hidden="true"></i></span>
                        <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse1"><i class="fa fa-folder-open-o fa-fw text-muted"></i> BluFractal Overview</a>

                    </h4>
                </div>
                <div id="collapse1" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                    <div class="panel-body">
                        <div class="alert alert-warning">
                            <p><em>Our algorithm recalculates the data on the BluFractal System screen at the end of each trading session.  All information on the screen is relevant to the last completed trading day.</em></p>
                            <p><i class="fa fa-lightbulb-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> &nbsp; <strong>Tip:</strong> You can use the daily Trend and Fail Point indicators for directional confirmation of your intra-day trades.</p>
                        </div>
                        <h4><i class="fa fa-list-alt" aria-hidden="true"></i> Trend Indicator</h4>
                        <p>
                            Confirms directional trend of the security's price and that trend-following trading positions are recommended.<br />
                            <span class="trend_text">
                                Positive Trend = Blue Bars</br>
                                Negative Trend = Purple Bars</br>
                                Neutral Market = Gray Bars</br>
                            </span>

                            <em>Probability models show that trades placed consistent with the fractal trend have a statistically significant performance improvement compared to conventional analytical techniques.</em>
                        </p>
                        <h4><i class="fa fa-list-alt" aria-hidden="true"></i> Fail Point</h4>
                        <p>
                            The price-point that our fractal algorithm projects the current trend will fail.<br />

                            <em>Neutral markets are marked N/A for this value.  If the value displays “UNK”, then the algorithm needs more data to accurately project the fail point (it typically takes a few trading days after the beginning of a new trend for enough data to calculate this value).</em>
                        </p>
                        <h4><i class="fa fa-list-alt" aria-hidden="true"></i> Meter</h4>
                        <p>The projected time remaining in the current trend.  All trends begin with the Meter at the very top of the scale. </p>
                        <h4><i class="fa fa-list-alt" aria-hidden="true"></i> Starting Date</h4>
                        <p>The trade day that the current trend began. </p>
                        <h4><i class="fa fa-list-alt" aria-hidden="true"></i> Starting Price </h4>
                        <p>The price at which the current trend began. </p>
                        <h4><i class="fa fa-list-alt" aria-hidden="true"></i> Days in Trend </h4>
                        <p>The number of days since the current trend began. </p>
                    </div>
                    @*<div class="panel-footer">Panel Footer</div>*@
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <div class="panel-heading">
                    <h4 class="panel-title pannel_bg_blue">
                        <span class="option_icons"><i class="fa fa-file-pdf-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> <i class="fa fa-print" aria-hidden="true"></i></span>
                        <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse2"><i class="fa fa-folder-open-o fa-fw text-muted"></i> BluNeural Overview</a>
                    </h4>
                </div>
                <div id="collapse2" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                    <div class="panel-body">
                        <div class="alert alert-warning">
                            <p><em>Our algorithm recalculates the data on the BluNeural System screen at the end of each trading session.  All information on the screen is relevant to the last completed trading day.</em></p>
                            <p><i class="fa fa-lightbulb-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> &nbsp; <strong>Tip:</strong> You can use the daily Zone and Pivot indicators for directional confirmation of your intra-day trades.</p>
                        </div>
                        <h4><i class="fa fa-list-alt" aria-hidden="true"></i> Zone Indicator </h4>
                        <p>
                            Signals an imminent Price Pivot (Up or Down) for the security and that counter-trend trading positions are recommend. The Zone Indicator reflects the inital change in price behavior before the actual turn in price (or simultaneously to it) is confirmed by the Pivot Indicator.<br />

                            <em>Green Bars for Buy Zones.  Red Bars for Sell Zones.  Probability models show that pivot signals derived from neural network data have a statistically significant performance improvement compared to conventional mean-reversion techniques.</em>

                        </p>
                        <h4><i class="fa fa-list-alt" aria-hidden="true"></i> Pivot Indicator </h4>
                        <p>
                            Shows the direction of the last price pivot of the security and confirms the turn in price signaled by the Zone Indicator. <br />

                            <em>Probability models show that pivot-point data derived from neural networks have a statistically significant performance improvement compared to conventional mean-reversion techniques.</em>

                        </p>
                        <h4><i class="fa fa-list-alt" aria-hidden="true"></i> Starting Date </h4>
                        <p>The trade day that the current Zone began.</p>
                        <h4><i class="fa fa-list-alt" aria-hidden="true"></i> Duration </h4>
                        <p>The number of days since the current Zone began.</p>
                        <h4><i class="fa fa-list-alt" aria-hidden="true"></i> Last Up Pivot  </h4>
                        <p>The date of the last Up price pivot of the security.</p>
                        <h4><i class="fa fa-list-alt" aria-hidden="true"></i> Last Down Pivot  </h4>
                        <p>The date of the last Down price pivot of the security.</p>
                    </div>
                    @*<div class="panel-footer">Panel Footer</div>*@
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <div class="panel-heading">
                    <h4 class="panel-title pannel_bg_blue">
                        <span class="option_icons"><i class="fa fa-file-pdf-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> <i class="fa fa-print" aria-hidden="true"></i></span>
                        <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse3"><i class="fa fa-folder-open-o fa-fw text-muted"></i> BluQuant Overview</a>
                    </h4>
                </div>
                <div id="collapse3" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                    <div class="panel-body">
                        <div class="alert alert-warning">
                            <p><em>Our algorithm calculates the data for the Buy and Sell signals generated by the BluQuant System during the current market session in real-time.  Once a security is opened with a Buy Signal it is placed into the Current Portfolio.  Then, when the Sell Signal for that security is issued, it is moved to the Completed Trades List.  To maximize investment returns, BluQuant has been calibrated for use in Margined Brokerage Accounts (for more conservative investors a cash-based account can be used).</em></p>
                            <p><i class="fa fa-lightbulb-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> &nbsp; <strong>Tip:</strong> You can use the BluQuant positions for directional confirmation of intra-day trades on those stocks.</p>
                        </div>
                        <h4><i class="fa fa-list-alt" aria-hidden="true"></i> Today’s Signals  </h4>
                        <p>
                            The current day’s live trade signals that are Alerted here and simultaneously sent to you each day via email as they are generated.  <br />

                            <em>There are typically 1 to 7 new positions triggered per week.  Each position’s holding period averages approximately 6 weeks (however, some could just be a few days while others could last a few months).  It is recommended that users execute these trades at the triggered price and time (or as close as possible) for best performance results.</em>

                        </p>
                        <h4><i class="fa fa-list-alt" aria-hidden="true"></i> Buy Signal   </h4>
                        <p>
                            Lists the security’s exchange symbol and the price and time that the Buy Signal to open this position was triggered that day.  User’s should attempt to execute at, or below, the triggered price.  <br />
                            <em>Users are not required to purchase every Buy Signal generated by the system.  Use discretion based upon the number of open positions desired in your portfolio and current funds available for trading.</em>

                        </p>
                        <h4><i class="fa fa-list-alt" aria-hidden="true"></i> Sell Signal </h4>
                        <p>
                            Lists the security’s exchange symbol and the price and time that the Sell Signal to exit the position was triggered that day.  User’s should attempt to execute at, or above, the triggered price.<br />
                            <em>However, it is recommended for users to close their position that day because once the security has triggered its Sell Signal it is removed from the Current Portfolio and is no longer tracked by our system. </em>

                        </p>
                        <h4><i class="fa fa-list-alt" aria-hidden="true"></i> Current Portfolio </h4>
                        <p>The list of all open positions currently in the BluQuant System Portfolio.</p>
                        <h4><i class="fa fa-list-alt" aria-hidden="true"></i> Last 10 Trades </h4>
                        <p>A list of the 10 most recently completed trades.  Completed trades are positions that were triggered with a Buy Signal and then were subsequently closed by a following Sell Signal for that security. The "Result" data is based upon the use of a 2:1  margin account.</p>
                    </div>
                    @*<div class="panel-footer">Panel Footer</div>*@
                </div>
            </div>

        <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title pannel_bg_blue">
                    <span class="option_icons"><i class="fa fa-file-pdf-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> <i class="fa fa-print" aria-hidden="true"></i></span>
